Media notes: Eurasian Blackbird immature Michael's Ave. Reserve Auckland 14/12/17
Observation Details: A fledgling closely followed an adult male on mown grass at the northern edge of the Michael's Park School playing field.  The adult moved away onto the field, while the fledgling stayed, uttering soft harsh calls and pecking briefly at an overhanging stem and a grass head below and to one side.  I thought it was likely learning to coordinate its sight and bill movements and in contrast to a grass head, that a thick stem was hard and unyielding when pecked.  Other adults foraging in mown grass and in plant litter under trees and shrubs at different places around the reserve.

Media notes: Eurasian Blackbird immature Michael's Ave. Reserve Auckland 14/12/17
Observation Details: A fledgling closely followed an adult male on mown grass at the northern edge of the Michael's Park School playing field.  The adult moved away onto the field, while the fledgling stayed, uttering soft harsh calls and pecking briefly at an overhanging stem and a grass head below and to one side.  I thought it was likely learning to coordinate its sight and bill movements and in contrast to a grass head, that a thick stem was hard and unyielding when pecked.  Other adults foraging in mown grass and in plant litter under trees and shrubs at different places around the reserve.
